The error message text is from AWS/EC2:

{code}
$ aws ec2 register-image --name '!!! invalid name "%^&*{}' --block-device-mappings '{"": ""}' --root-device-name /dev/sda1
{
    "Response": {
        "Errors": {
            "Error": {
                "Message": "AMI names must be between 3 and 128 characters long, and may contain letters, numbers, '(', ')', '.', '-', '/' and '_'", 
                "Code": "InvalidAMIName.Malformed"
            }
        }, 
        "RequestID": "fbb01541-a80f-4af1-bf08-dd0791d66400"
    }
}
A client error (InvalidAMIName.Malformed) occurred: AMI names must be between 3 and 128 characters long, and may contain letters, numbers, '(', ')', '.', '-', '/' and '_'
{code}

That said, it looks like there is an inconsistency between the error message and what is actually permitted.

*Update*

Ran into this in Eucalyptus 4.0.0 (4.0.0-0.0.899.20140418gitc8ca752d.el6.x86_64):
{code}
[root@odc-d-31 ~]# euca-register -n ubuntu-trusty-14.04-x86_64 ubuntu-trusty-x86_64/trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64.img.manifest.xml
euca-register: error (InvalidAMIName.Malformed): AMI names must be between 3 and 128 characters long, and may contain letters, numbers, '(', ')', '.', '-', '/' and '_'
{code}
